Version 0.6.3 (2014-03-11):

        * Maintenance realease. Fixes linking error (-soname) using modern 
	  libtool (2.4.x) and autoconf (2.69).

Version 0.6.2 (2008-05-26):

	* Maintenance relese that fixes small errors in the installation.
	  The Simca QP library path should now be auto-detected if installed
	  in common directory pathes (like /usr/local/libchemgps a.s.o.).
	
	* Fixed compiler warnings about unused variables.
	
	* Memory leaks (reported by valgrind) should be fixed as long as possible.
	
Version 0.6.1 (2008-04-09):
	
	* This is a maintenance release that fixes documentation errors in
	  the manual page for the library.
	  
Version 0.6.0 (2008-04-09):

	* Split the code into two packages: applications (chemgps-sqp2) and 
	  a library part (this code). This code now fully support writing
	  client/server code using both local (UNIX) and network (TCP) sockets.

*** Historical notes from chemgps-sqp (the standalone only version):

Version 0.5.2 (2008-03-03):

	* Modified code to reorder quantitative input data against the
	  variable order in the project if input data contains a descriptor
	  header. This also filters unused varibles from input data.
	  
	* Adding batch job mode. This mode suppress info messages from
	  SIMCA-QP and warnings messages caused by batch queue command pipe.

Version 0.5.1 (2008-02-19):

	* Changed output to be less verbose (stripping result headers). The
	  old behavour is restored by using the --verbose option.
	  
	* Adding XML format output option.
	
Version 0.5.0 (2008-02-18):

	* First working version (result for TPS output verified).
	
